<br>
Diablita Di'Asmodea<br>
54th Rake of the Shadows <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucaillougna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 556<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 10:46:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2827.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Necros in general</span><hr size=1> ((<br>
I second the comment about not being afraid of grouping or not grouping based on RP if you intend to RP (and if you don't, why play here).  No, you would -never- be welcomed by a percentage of the server, Caillou included (Teir'dal necro is the epitome of evil to her, with Teir'dal shadow knight a close second, other shadow knights after that, but not, oddly, other necros), but isn't that the point of the light vs dark conflict?<br>
<br>
There are several Teir'dal and other evils who roleplay so you should be able to find enough grouping if you look for it.  Get to know people on server and on the boards (check out some of the guild boards of the evils, or even the good/neutrals) and start forming opinions about people and the guilds.  A lot of RP guilds are not level restricted.<br>
<br>
Good luck, have fun!  <br>
))<br>
<br>
Oh, no, not more Teir'dal scum.  Worse... a necromancer.  And there are those, once neutral, who say they must side with evil to balance good. *sigh*<br>
